I recommend using `exists`:

    select a.name, 
           (exists (select 1
                    from tableB b 
                    where a.id = b.id_tabel_A
                   )
           ) as status
    from tableA a; 

The reason I prefer `exists` is that it automatically handles duplicates in `tableB`.  You don&#39;t have to worry about the query returning duplicate results.

